UEFA has announced the Champions League team of the 2020/21 season. The 2020/21 Champions League season ended on Saturday night with Chelsea’s 1-0 defeat of Manchester City in the final in Porto, Portugal. Kai Havertz’s first-half goal gave Chelsea the victory over Pep Guardiola’s side. Below is UEFA’s team for the 2020/21 season; Goalkeeper: Édouard Mendy (Chelsea) – 66 points Defenders: Kyle Walker (Man. City) – 62 points Antonio Rüdiger (Chelsea) – 63 points Rúben Dias (Man. City) – 60 points César Azpilicueta (Chelsea) – 61 points Midfielders: İlkay Gündoğan (Man. City) – 58 points Jorginho (Chelsea) – 57 points Phil Foden (Man. City) – 65 points Forwards: Mohamed Salah (Liverpool) – 63 points Erling Haaland (Dortmund) – 62 points Kylian Mbappé (Paris Saint-Germain) – 61 points EPL: Guardiola reveals points Man City need to be champions amid Man Utd’s fight 